Some needed tools:

bootstrapper -  
*see all bootstrap classes at https://www.w3schools.com/bootstrap4/bootstrap_ref_all_classes.asp
*or https://hackerthemes.com/bootstrap-cheatsheet/
  install - npm i bootstrapper
  import - (in index.js) - import 'bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.css'
  



*********************************
How to set up github on VSCODE:
*********************************

Steps:
Create a directory on the local file system.
Create a repo on Github.
Select Clone "Clone or download" on Github, copy the link
In Visual Studio Code, sect File -> Add Folder to Workspace -> Select the newly created directory
Select Terminal Window
In the window, type:
git config --global user.name <github userID>

git clone <URL from github link copied earlier>
That should be all that's required.  any newly created file should be available on github after stage/commit/push.
